<br>
First off. I didn't roll sar up the day you met her. She's been around for a very long time, and as such, has dealt with a good number of people. What happened was a long time coming, and would have happened the same way, right under Inthul's nose.  Add to that, other ooc factors, that you and I discussed(no, peanut gallery, some things aren't mine to tell), I, as I told you, felt better moving Sar's story on.<br>
<br>
The only thing that bugged me, was the fact that you were fine with and fine with it, till it actually happened...and I had worried myself stupid because I knew you would take it harder than you let on.  <br>
<br>
Now, having a recruit tell me that we're a lightbringer guild, just pissed me off.<br>
<br>
Yes we have a halfelf. That'd be me. The League(Still the premier evil guild on FV, HoD aspires.) had me...and has a halfelf currently.<br>
<br>
Under the old alignment rules, gnomes of Ralloz Zek could choose to be neutral evil, whereas, say..woodelves of Zek, could not.  Wizards were explained outstandingly, as always, by Eliezer(Welcome back, old friend, by the way), and to call us a lightbringer guild(you can say you did it IC, we both know better), just negates the work we officers have put into it.<br>
<br>
I'm a good deal calmer than I was last night, and for what it's worth, J..PoInthul, I'm still sorry to see you go. There was far more to Inthul than Sarhea, for certain...and even though you've a tendency to mingle the two, you're a damn fine roleplayer, and you should rethink your decision.<br>
<br>
