<br>
Comparing an MMORPG like EQ to an RPG like D&amp;D is inherently flawed.<br>
<br>
A D&amp;D encounter is designed by the DM to be appropriate to his group of players.<br>
<br>
EverQuest encounters are designed by Verant/SOE to require certain particular elements, and it designs those encounters without ANY regard to Roleplaying, except in the smallest sense that a particular Faction might be required.<br>
<br>
That is not to say I disagree with you that making contrived excuses to bring in a Class that is deemed 'necessary' isn't somewhat lame -- I just disagree that Alignment is in any way a 'balancing factor' in EQ.  Factions are the closest thing that EQ has to Roleplaying balance.<br>
